Inheritance:
1.inherition is the process of creating a new class from a exsiting class where the existing class is called super class and new class is called sub class
Advantages of Inheritance:
1.code enchanceability(version control)
2.code reuseability
Encapsulation:
1.declaring private variable in class and accesssing those variable through a public method and name those method as setter or getter that kind of class is called encapsulation.
-data hiding
Polymorphism:
Ability of an object to behave diffrently
-runtime=overriding
-compiletime=overloading
Static Keyword: when you want every obj of the class to have the same value and if one obj change the value all obj shoud have that exact value
This keyword: represent curent class obj
Super keyword: represent parent class obj
interface-blueprint or template for a class

Lambda expression-it is an short form of anonymous function that always implements with functional interface.
How to declare- ()->{};

Types of Lambda expression: 
1.No parameter, no return value 
()->{
    System.out.println("this is lambda expression);
    System.out.println("this is lambda expression);
};
OR
()->System.out.println("this is lambda expression); // for single line 

2.no parameter, with return value
()->{
    int n1=10, n2=20;
    return(n1+n2);
};
OR
()-> "Lambda expression"; //in single line their shouldn't be return keyword 
()->20;
3.with one parameter, no return value 
(int n)-> System.out.println(n*n);
(n)->System.out.println(n*n);
n->System.out.println(n*n);
n->(n>10)?Sytem.out.println("yes"):Sytem.out.println(no);
4.with one parameter, with return value
(int num)->num+10;
(num)->num+20;
num->num+30;
5.with multiple parameter,no return value
(int n1,int n2)->Sytem.out.println("sum:"+(n1+n2));
6.with multiple parameter, with return value 
(int n1,int n2)->n1+n2;
(int n1,int n2)->{return n1+n2};

